<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2011-03-26</DATELINE><TITLE>Intensive Care Medicine: Where We Are and Where We Want To Go?</TITLE><BODY>Intensive care medicine can be defined as the science and art of detecting and managing patients with impending or established critical illness, in order to prevent further deterioration and revert the disease process or its consequences, so as to achieve the best possible outcomes.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>